%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c8710d1c84a0eaca81fcc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22310%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Laura%20McCamy%2C%20and%20her%20wife.%3Cp%3ELaura%20McCamy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhen%20my%20California%20marriage%20to%20my%20wife%20became%20legal%20federally%20in%202015%2C%20we%20could%20finally%20file%20taxes%20jointly.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMarriage%20has%20allowed%20us%20to%20share%20health%20insurance%20benefits.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20legal%20right%20to%20marry%20guarantees%20our%20spousal%20property%20rights%20and%20makes%20me%20feel%20financially%20secure.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20almost%2010%20years%20since%20the%20federal%20government%20legally%20recognized%20my%20marriage%2C%20and%20it's%20easy%20to%20become%20complacent%20and%20forget%20what%20life%20was%20like%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20remember%20all%20I've%20gained.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20conservative%20majority%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20signaled%20its%20willingness%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjustice-thomas-said-the-court-should-reconsider-rulings-on-same-sex-marriage-2022-6%5C%22%3Etake%20away%20the%20right%20for%20same-sex%20couples%20to%20marry%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Here%20are%20just%20a%20few%20of%20the%20many%20financial%20advantages%20of%20being%20married%20that%20are%20still%20at%20stake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFiling%20a%20joint%20tax%20return%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20when%20my%20partner%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20get%20%26quot%3Bmarried%26quot%3B%20in%201995%20%E2%80%94%20we%20jumped%20over%20a%20broom%20because%20we%20had%20no%20way%20to%20legally%20marry%20at%20that%20time%20%E2%80%94%20checking%20the%20box%20for%20%26quot%3Bsingle%26quot%3B%20on%20tax%20returns%20felt%20like%20a%20demeaning%20lie%2C%20but%20we%20had%20no%20choice%20because%20the%20government%20didn't%20recognize%20our%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%202008%2C%20the%20California%20Supreme%20Court%20legalized%20same-sex%20marriage%2C%20and%20we%20were%20legally%20married%20in%20our%20home%20state.%20But%20we%20still%20had%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProp%208%20passed%20in%20November%202008%2C%20making%20same-sex%20marriage%20once%20again%20illegal%20in%20California.%20Our%20tax%20returns%20got%20really%20complicated.%20We%20could%20file%20jointly%20in%20California%2C%20but%20the%20federal%20government%20still%20considered%20us%20single%2C%20so%20our%20tax%20preparer%20had%20to%20reconcile%20the%20numbers%20between%20our%20two%20returns%2C%20costing%20us%20extra%20money%20in%20tax%20prep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20the%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court%20legalized%20same-sex%20marriage%20nationally%2C%20and%20that's%20when%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20started%20to%20truly%20reap%20the%20benefits%20of%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20married%20couples%20save%20money%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fshould-i-file-taxes-jointly-or-separately-married%5C%22%3Efiling%20taxes%20jointly%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that's%20certainly%20been%20true%20for%20my%20wife%20and%20me.%20We%20saved%20on%20taxes%20when%20she%20returned%20to%20school%20while%20I%20was%20working.%20We%20saved%20when%20I%20made%20a%20career%20change%2C%20and%20my%20earnings%20dipped%20for%20a%20while.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBest%20of%20all%2C%20we%20can%20check%20the%20%26quot%3Bmarried%26quot%3B%20box%20on%20our%20tax%20returns%20and%20every%20other%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPre-tax%20insurance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20currently%20get%20my%20health%20insurance%20through%20my%20wife's%20work%2C%20and%20the%20amount%20is%20taken%20out%20before%20tax.%20That%20means%20she%20doesn't%20pay%20income%20tax%20on%20the%20cost%20of%20my%20health%20insurance%2C%20saving%20us%20the%20taxes%20on%20about%20%2412%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20we%20were%20legally%20married%2C%20my%20wife%20had%20health%20insurance%20through%20her%20job%2C%20but%20she%20wasn't%20able%20to%20add%20me%20to%20the%20policy.%20The%20insurer%20could%20choose%20whether%20to%20recognize%20same-sex%20spouses%2C%20and%20it%20chose%20not%20to.%20I%20couldn't%20afford%20insurance%20at%20that%20time%2C%20so%20I%20was%20uninsured.%20By%20the%20time%20she%20quit%20her%20job%20to%20go%20to%20grad%20school%2C%20I%20could%20put%20her%20on%20my%20work%20insurance%2C%20but%20I%20had%20to%20pay%20income%20tax%20on%20the%20cost%2C%20because%20the%20federal%20government%20didn't%20yet%20recognize%20our%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20able%20to%20share%20coverage%20benefits%20our%20physical%20and%20financial%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOwning%20property%20together%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20bought%20our%20condo%20in%202004%2C%20we%20weren't%20legally%20married%2C%20so%20we%20couldn't%20just%20let%20the%20title%20company%20take%20care%20of%20the%20deed.%20We%20had%20to%20consult%20an%20attorney%20to%20make%20sure%20our%20ownership%20interests%20were%20described%20in%20a%20way%20that%20gave%20us%20rights%20as%20close%20to%20spouses%20as%20possible%2C%20an%20extra%20expense%20married%20couples%20don't%20incur.%20Now%2C%20our%20deed%20reflects%20our%20status%20as%20a%20married%20couple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20is%20a%20community%20property%20state%2C%20so%20property%20acquired%20during%20marriage%20is%20assumed%20to%20belong%20equally%20to%20both%20spouses.%20That%20includes%20more%20than%20real%20estate.%20I%20worked%20for%20an%20attorney%20who%20helped%20gay%20couples%20with%20estate%20planning%20and%20probate%20before%20marriage%20equality%2C%20and%20we%20occasionally%20had%20homophobic%20families%20sweep%20in%20and%20take%20all%20the%20belongings%20from%20an%20apartment%20after%20one%20member%20of%20the%20couple%20died.%20Without%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-much-does-it-cost-to-make-a-will%5C%22%3Ewill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20many%20people%20don't%20have%2C%20the%20surviving%20partner%20had%20no%20rights%20to%20the%20possessions%20in%20his%20own%20home.%20Now%2C%20marriage%20protects%20our%20rights%20to%20our%20joint%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFreedom%20from%20financial%20fear%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20decision%20to%20legalize%20same-sex%20marriage%20in%202015%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20a%20full%20citizen%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20I%20didn't%20recognize%20the%20base%20level%20of%20financial%20insecurity%20I%20had%20lived%20with%20until%20it%20was%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20relish%20the%20opportunity%20to%20lead%20an%20average%20and%20slightly%20boring%20life%20regardless%20of%20whom%20I%20married.%20And%20I%20will%20continue%20to%20reap%20the%20financial%20rewards%20of%20being%20married%20in%20the%20future%2C%20including%20spousal%20retirement%20benefits%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-social-security%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20my%20wife's%20pension.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20our%20rights%20and%20recognition%20of%20our%20marriage%20are%20threatened%2C%20I%20will%20be%20on%20the%20frontlines%20again%2C%20fighting%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20that%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarriage-equality-gave-my-wife-and-me-access-to-crucial-benefits-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719661442000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c8709d1c84a0eaca81fc4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarriage-equality-gave-my-wife-and-me-access-to-crucial-benefits-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20wife%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20get%20married%20in%201995%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20until%202015%20that%20the%20federal%20government%20guaranteed%20us%20the%20financial%20benefits%20others%20get.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Laura%20McCamy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarriage-equality-gave-my-wife-and-me-access-to-crucial-benefits-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20gave%20my%20daughter%20an%20uncommon%20name.%20People%20always%20pronounce%20it%20wrong%20but%20I%20still%20love%20it.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225167%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mom%20holding%20her%20baby%20by%20a%20dimly%20lit%20window.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667b090550b021b5cae95e4f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223445%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EStanislaw%20Pytel%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20name%20Sara%20is%20pretty%20common%2C%20especially%20spelled%20with%20an%20h.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20named%20my%20daughter%20Charissa%20Anne%2C%20giving%20her%20an%20uncommon%20name%20first.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20was%20a%20popular%20name%20decades%20ago%2C%20but%20now%20it's%20popularity%20has%20dwindled%20and%20that's%20why%20I%20chose%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20named%20after%20my%20great%20grandmother%20on%20my%20father's%20side%20and%20my%20great-great%20aunt%20on%20my%20mother's.%20My%20name%20also%20appeared%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-names-most-popular-by-decade-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20top%2010%20girls%20names%3C%2Fa%3E%20lists%20throughout%20the%2080s%2C%20so%20everywhere%20I%20went%20there%20was%20another%20Sara(h).%20Even%20in%20my%20small%20high%20school%20graduating%20class%20of%2050%2C%20there%20was%20another%20Sarah.%20I%20went%20to%20college%20and%20there%20were%20two%20other%20Sarahs%20just%20on%20my%20dorm%20hallway.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20I%20started%20being%20known%20by%20a%20nickname.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Sarahs%20with%20an%20h%20are%20about%20three%20times%20more%20common%20than%20those%20without%2C%20it%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-names-spelling-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefault%20spelling%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20spelling%20people%20even%20use%20when%20replying%20to%20emails%20signed%20with%20the%20correct%20spelling.%20I%20have%20a%20friend%20that%20I've%20known%20for%20almost%2010%20years%20that%20still%20spells%20my%20name%20wrong.%20At%20some%20point%20I%20just%20gave%20up%20on%20correcting%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20married%20a%20man%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgave-child-common-name-no-regrets-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommon%20name%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20well.%20Even%20worse%2C%20he%20is%20a%20junior%2C%20so%20he%20has%20the%20same%20first%20and%20middle%20name%20as%20his%20father.%20Childhood%20family%20gatherings%20were%20even%20more%20confusing%2C%20because%20he%20also%20had%20a%20grandfather%2C%20uncle%2C%20and%20cousin%20who%20shared%20his%20first%20name.%20Nicknames%20were%20necessary%20so%20everyone%20knew%20who%20you%20were%20talking%20to%20and%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22828d0206-d77d-4f33-a036-c69ba8f87b08%5C%22%3EWe%20wanted%20to%20name%20our%20child%20something%20that%20wasn't%20popular%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223036%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20holding%20baby%20for%20a%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667b095fd1c84a0eaca7ba1e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222277%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20(right)%20and%20her%20husband%20have%20pretty%20common%20names%2C%20so%20they%20gave%20their%20daughter%20a%20less%20common%20one.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20started%20talking%20about%20future%20children%2C%20we%20knew%20we%20wouldn't%20be%20naming%20them%20either%20a%20family%20name%20or%20a%20popular%2C%20common%20name.%20We%20wanted%20them%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-kids-have-uncommon-names-they-like-them-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enames%20that%20felt%20more%20special%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ones%20that%20they%20wouldn't%20encounter%20too%20many%20other%20people%20with%2C%20if%20at%20all.%20But%20we%20also%20didn't%20want%20to%20name%20them%20something%20too%20unusual%2C%20that%20they%20could%20potentially%20be%20made%20fun%20of%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20got%20pregnant%20we%20started%20brainstorming.%20I%20always%20thought%20that%20if%20I%20had%20a%20girl%20I%20would%20name%20her%20after%20my%20favorite%20literary%20character%2C%20Anne%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbooks-that-changed-our-lives-2016-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnne%20of%20Green%20Gables%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spunky%20creative%20who%20also%20had%20to%20correct%20people%20that%20spelled%20her%20name%20wrong.%20Anne%20has%20been%20out%20of%20vogue%20as%20a%20popular%20girls%20name%20for%20decades%2C%20but%20it%20is%20a%20classic%20girls%20name%20that%20already%20belonged%20to%20multiple%20people%20we%20knew%2C%20including%20an%20extended%20family%20member.%20So%20it%20ended%20up%20being%20demoted%20to%20a%20middle%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20the%20gut%20feeling%20that%20the%20baby%20was%20a%20girl%20long%20before%20we%20officially%20found%20out%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fhow-many-ultrasounds-during-pregnancy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egender%20scan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20just%20like%20I%20had%20the%20gut%20feeling%20that%20a%20name%20I%20came%20across%20early%20in%20the%20pregnancy%20was%20her%20name%3A%20Charissa.%20It%20felt%20even%20more%20right%20when%20I%20did%20an%20online%20search%20and%20saw%20it%20hadn't%20cracked%20the%20top%201%2C000%20since%20the%201980s.%20There%20were%20three%20variations%20on%20the%20spelling%20and%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20chose%20the%20one%20that%20we%20liked%20the%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e15537d4-8d53-4fd7-b7d0-659de4cefe33%5C%22%3EI%20didn't%20realize%20people%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20pronounce%20Charissa%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20we%20didn't%20anticipate%20was%20that%20there%20would%20be%20confusion%20about%20how%20to%20pronounce%20it.%20The%20first%20visit%20to%20the%20pediatrician's%20office%20when%20her%20name%20was%20called%2C%20pronounced%20incorrectly%2C%20was%20the%20first%20time%20that%20it%20occurred%20to%20me.%20I%20initially%20dismissed%20it%20as%20one%20person%20pronouncing%20it%20wrong%2C%20but%20then%20it%20seemed%20like%20everyone%20who%20was%20encountering%20her%20name%20in%20written%20form%20first%20was%20getting%20it%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20become%20a%20pleasant%20surprise%20when%20someone%20pronounces%20it%20correctly.%20While%20anyone%20that%20she%20has%20regular%20in