%3ECaptain%20Theresa%20Claiborne%20signed%20up%20to%20the%20Air%20Force%20in%201980%2C%20and%20later%20worked%20as%20a%20captain%20for%20United%20Airlines.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20was%20below%20the%20height%20requirement%20and%20the%20first%20Black%20woman%20recruited%20to%20the%20Force.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EClaiborne%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20about%20the%20hurdles%20she%20faced%20and%20why%20piloting%20is%20a%20great%20career.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Captain%20Theresa%20Claiborne%2C%20the%20first%20Black%20female%20pilot%20in%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20and%20a%20captain%20at%20United.%20The%20following%20was%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20spent%20my%20younger%20days%20bouncing%20all%20over%20the%20world%20because%20my%20father%20was%20in%20the%20military.%20But%20life%20felt%20so%20stationary%20when%20we%20returned%20to%20the%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20college%2C%20I%20applied%20to%20the%20Reserve%20Office%20Training%20Corps%20(ROTC)%20in%20Berkeley.%20During%20the%20six-week%20training%20camp%2C%20they%20took%20us%20up%20on%20a%20T-37%20%5Ba%20small%20training%20plane%20made%20by%20Cessna%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlying%20a%20plane%20is%20freeing.%20It's%20this%20amazing%20feeling%20of%20control%20but%20no%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20right%20then%3A%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20pilot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d6519485-62a2-47d6-bb3a-b0ab980c1a58%5C%22%3EThe%20hardest%20period%20of%20my%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201980%2C%20the%20Air%20Force%20only%20had%2010%20slots%20for%20women%20per%20graduating%20class%2C%20and%20they%20had%20already%20been%20filled%20for%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20halfway%20through%20my%20junior%20year%2C%20they%20came%20back%20and%20said%20the%20women%20seemed%20to%20be%20graduating%20at%20the%20same%20rate%20as%20the%20men%2C%20so%20the%20allotment%20was%20increased%20to%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20flew%20out%20to%20Laughlin%20Air%20Force%20base%20in%20Texas%20to%20start%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-new-air-force-recruits-go-through-in-boot-camp-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epilot%20training%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22581%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Captain%20Theresa%20Claiborne%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667593e0886e840164bebea8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22581%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECaptain%20Theresa%20Claiborne%3Cp%3ECaptain%20Theresa%20Claiborne%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20daunting%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20in%20my%20class%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20prior%20flying%20experience.%20And%20when%20you're%20in%20training%2C%20flying%20is%20a%20lot%20like%20a%20loop-the-loop%20on%20a%20roller%20coaster%E2%80%A6%20but%20I'm%20not%20one%20for%20roller%20coasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20was%20just%20trying%20to%20get%20the%20task%20done%20and%20not%20be%20fearful%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20high%20school%2C%20my%20teacher%20said%20it%20was%20fine%20for%20me%20to%20be%20bad%20at%20Math%20because%20I%20could%20do%20English.%20But%20in%20training%2C%20everybody%20knew%20the%20instructors'%20formulas%2C%20and%20I%20didn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20my%20classmates%20were%20out%20having%20a%20good%20time%20on%20the%20weekends%2C%20I%20was%20back%20at%20the%20dorm%20studying.%20It%20was%20probably%20the%20hardest%20period%20of%20my%20life%20that%20year.%20I%20was%20lonely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20almost%20didn't%20make%20it%20to%20that%20point%20because%20I%20was%20short.%20You%20are%20supposed%20to%20be%20five%20feet%20four%20inches%2C%20and%20I%20was%20five%20feet%20two%20inches.%20For%20my%20entire%20career%2C%20I've%20had%20to%20stand%20on%20the%20balls%20of%20my%20feet%20when%20I%20was%20measured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3