%20country%20and%20of%20the%20base%2C%20and%20he%20failed%20to%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe're%20still%20far%20from%20our%20convention.%20And%20there%20is%20time%20for%20this%20party%20to%20figure%20out%20a%20different%20way%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20did%20land%20a%20few%20blows%20on%20his%20predecessor%20over%20Trump's%20various%20personal%20indiscretions%20and%20the%20January%206%202021%20insurrection%20on%20the%20US%20Capitol%2C%20saying%20at%20one%20point%2C%20%E2%80%9Cyou've%20got%20the%20morals%20of%20an%20alley%20cat%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20not%20enough%20to%20persuade%20many%20sceptics%20that%20Biden%20is%20capable%20of%20fighting%20off%20the%20Trump%20campaign%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20performing%20the%20duties%20of%20US%20commander-in-chief%20and%20the%20hardest%20job%20in%20the%20world%20for%20another%20four%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20polls%20over%20the%20weekend%20show%20Biden%20is%20losing%20support%20after%20his%20dreadful%20debate%20performance%2C%20which%20seems%20highly%20likely%2C%20the%20move%20to%20replace%20him%20as%20the%20Democrats'%20candidate%20will%20become%20even%20more%20intense%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20irresistible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20would%20this%20play%20out%20in%20the%20next%20few%20weeks%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EPersuading%20Biden%20to%20step%20aside%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20withering%20criticism%20from%20his%20party%2C%20Biden%20remains%20in%20control%20of%20his%20fate.%20He%20won%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalreview.com%2Fcorner%2Freminder-biden-has-3894-or-99-of-pledged-dnc-delegates%2F%5C%22%3E99%25%20of%20the%20pledged%20delegates%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Democratic%20primary%20process%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20meaning%20he%20is%20entitled%20to%20the%20nomination.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20any%20decision%20to%20move%20to%20a%20different%20candidate%20starts%20with%20Biden%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbsent%20dramatic%20health%20news%20or%20his%20removal%20under%20the%2025th%20amendment%20to%20the%20Constitution%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fhomenews%2Fhouse%2F4746165-speaker-johnson-cabinet-biden-25th-amendment%2F%5C%22%3Eallows%20for%20such%20action%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20vice%20president%20and%20a%20majority%20of%20his%20cabinet%20if%20the%20president%20is%20%E2%80%9Cunable%20to%20discharge%20the%20powers%20and%20duties%20of%20his%20office%E2%80%9D%2C%20Biden%20would%20have%20to%20agree%20to%20step%20down%20as%20the%20party's%20nominee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20should%20be%20realistic%20here%3A%20Biden%20is%20a%20very%20stubborn%20man.%20You%20don't%20get%20to%20be%20the%20president%20of%20the%20United%20States%20without%20being%20enormously%20self-confident.%20Biden%20may%20not%20be%20the%20smartest%20or%20most%20talented%20politician%2C%20but%20he%20is%20dogged%20and%20relentless%20in%20his%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20ran%20for%20president%20twice%20before%20his%20success%20in%202020.%20He%20didn't%20let%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpolitics%2F2024%2F05%2F14%2Fbiden-nearly-died-an-aneurysm-risky-surgery-changed-his-life%2F%5C%22%3Ebrain%20aneurysm%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1987%2F09%2F18%2Fus%2Fbiden-admits-plagiarism-in-school-but-says-it-was-not-malevolent.html%5C%22%3Eplagiarism%20charges%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FUS%2Ftimeline-hunter-biden-legal-political-scrutiny%2Fstory%3Fid%3D102293605%5C%22%3Efamilial%20dramas%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.com%2Fthis-day-in-history%2Fjoe-biden-loses-first-wife-and-daughter-in-tragic-car-accident%5C%22%3Epersonal%20tragedy%3C%2Fa%3E%20stop%20him%20seeking%20the%20highest%20office%20in%20the%20land.%20The%20day%20after%20the%20debate%20with%20Trump%2C%20he%20shook%20his%20fist%20at%20a%20campaign%20event%20in%20North%20Carolina%20and%20asserted%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20get%20knocked%20down%2C%20you%20get%20back%20up%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPersuading%20Biden%20to%20step%20down%20would%20require%20collaboration%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20First%20Lady%20Jill%20Biden.%20%E2%80%9CDr%20Jill%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20she%20is%20known%2C%20has%20taken%20a%20hands-on%20role%20in%20managing%20the%20president's%20daily%20life%20and%20public%20appearances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20very%20few%20Democratic%20Party%20elders%20who%20can%20be%20influential%20with%20the%20Bidens.%20The%20list%20probably%20starts%20and%20stops%20with%20former%20President%20Barack%20Obama%20and%20former%20House%20Speaker%20Nancy%20Pelosi.%20If%20those%20two%20go%20to%20the%20first%20lady%20and%20forcefully%20urge%20Biden's%20withdrawal%2C%20it%20could%20be%20very%20difficult%20to%20resist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20could%20Biden%20save%20face%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Biden%20withdraws%20from%20the%20race%20before%20the%20Democratic%20convention%20in%20mid-August%2C%20his%20delegates%20could%20then%20vote%20for%20a%20new%20nominee%20at%20the%20event.%20Potential%20nominees%20include%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%2C%20California%20Governor%20Gavin%20Newsom%2C%20Michigan%20Governor%20Gretchen%20Whitmer%20and%20Pennsylvania%20Governor%20Josh%20Shapiro.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20except%20for%20Harris%2C%20none%20of%20these%20candidates%20has%20been%20vetted%20publicly%20during%20the%20Democratic%20primary%20process%20for%20the%20world's%20most%20scrutinised%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Biden%20were%20to%20withdraw%20from%20the%20race%20after%20the%20convention%2C%20a%20special%20meeting%20of%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Democratic%20National%20Committee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdemocrats.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F2024-Call-for-Convention.pdf%5C%22%3Ewould%20decide%20on%20the%20new%20nominee%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20committee%20includes%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fpolitics%2F2024-election%2Fcan-democrats-replace-joe-biden-ballot-rcna159374%5C%22%3E500%20leading%20party%20members%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20all%20US%20states%20and%20territories.%20(Whitmer%20is%20one%20of%20three%20vice%20chairs.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20question%20senior%20Biden%20confidants%20might%20be%20asking%20themselves%20is%2C%20which%20scenario%20offers%20Biden%20a%20more%20graceful%20and%20successful%20exit%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20may%20want%20to%20anoint%20a%20successor%20and%20he%20would%20want%20to%20choose%20the%20method%20that%20offers%20him%20the%20most%20control.%20That%20may%20be%20the%20convention%20route%2C%20where%20he%20at%20least%20can%20claim%20the%20allegiance%20of%20his%20primary%20delegates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20require%20an%20announcement%20in%20the%20next%20few%20weeks.%20The%20sooner%20the%20better%2C%20so%20as%20to%20build%20as%20much%20public%20support%20as%20possible%20for%20a%20new%20nominee.%20Biden%20could%20salvage%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20his%20reputation%20if%20his%20handpicked%20successor%20then%20defeated%20Trump%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThings%20look%20grim%20for%20Democrats%20right%20now%2C%20but%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20they%20may%20be%20in%20a%20strong%20position.%20Trump%20is%20very%20unpopular%20with%20most%20Americans.%20The%202021%20insurrection%20remains%20a%20massive%20stain%20on%20his%20legacy.%20His%20vote%20ceiling%20among%20probable%20voters%20in%20November%20is%20still%20likely%20below%2050%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVeteran%20Obama%20strategist%20David%20Axelrod%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fhomenews%2Fcampaign%2F4745498-biden-debate-trump-challenge%2F%5C%22%3Ewarned%20Republicans%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20debate%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%2C%20for%20whatever%20reason%2C%20there's%20a%20change%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20ticket%2C%20you%20guys%20are%20in%20trouble%20with%20Donald%20Trump.%20Because%20the%20guy%20who%20was%20up%20th